message.content: <OUTPUT_TEXT>To gather and analyze research data, you should start by identifying the relevant legal issues and jurisdictions involved. Then, access legal databases such as Westlaw, LexisNexis, or government websites to find statutes, case law, and legal articles. Review the documents to extract pertinent information, ensuring to note any legal precedents or interpretations that may impact the case. Organize the data systematically, highlighting key points and discrepancies, and prepare a comprehensive report or memorandum summarizing your findings and their implications for the legal matter at hand.</OUTPUT_TEXT>
